[The location of the 5 outbreaks can be seen on the map at
http://www.abc.net.au/news/events/hendra-virus/. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ]

[The task force is important to explore ways to control the disease
so I hope some researchers are included who may have some insights but
as yet unpublished work.

Perhaps fencing off the fig trees so that horses are no longer
exposed to so much saliva, and perhaps excrement from the flying foxes
would be appropriate? The bats seem to be very sloppy when they eat
and figs seem to be a favorite food. There are fig trees on several of
the properties in quarantine.

So while there may be no clear cut answers there may be some simple
management techniques that may prove helpful. Certainly if the horses
are not under the trees they have less exposure to the bats and
therefore it should stand to reason less exposure to the virus. -
Mod.TG]
